le imagery in order to make his message more emphatic, the female body as such forms an integral part of their metaphors. The contributions in this volume explore this phenomenon within the literature of early Judaism, and within its broad environments.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aBible. New TestamentxCriticism, interpretation, etcxCongresses. 0aBible. Old TestamentxCriticism, interpretation, etcxCongesses. 0aHuman body in the BiblevCongresses. 0aHuman body in the BiblexCongresses. 0aMiddle Eastern literaturexHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aMiddle Eastern literaturexHistory and criticismxCongresses. 0aWomen in the BiblevCongresses. 0aWomen in the BiblexCongresses. 4aEarly Christianity. 4aEarly Judaism. 4aFrühes Christentum. 4aFrühes Judentum. 4aGenderrollen. 4aKonzepte von Weiblichkeit. 4afemininity. 4agender. 7aRELIGION / Christian Life / Women's Issues.2bisacsh1 aXeravits, Géza G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104101290 cprintz978311040653540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041009940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110410099423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110410099.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb